      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced</strong> <strong>onion </strong>and <strong>carrot </strong>and cook for 3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile dissolve the <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>Marmite</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in the <strong>soy sauce </strong>– this is your <strong>rich tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1707749339700-x200.jpg",
